      "writtenOn": "2026-05-28T08:52:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is not tied to one specific tool.\nThe intent is to make bmcweb self-contained and standards-complete for\nthe Redfish PrivilegeRegistry resource.\n\nWhy it is worth the binary hit:\n\nIt closes a standards gap in registry exposure.\nThe added data is static registry content (mostly read-only data), not\nan always-running background feature.\nIt is only exercised when the PrivilegeRegistry routes are requested, so\nnormal request paths are unchanged.\nKeeping the mapping in-tree avoids runtime external dependency and keeps\nbehavior deterministic/offline-safe.",
      "parentUuid": "9b78fba1_a645d56c",
      "revId": "b6a74f2f93dafa1a98914b2c9e2f8093cc97864f",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
